body:
In the light of #3648 and while troubleshooting https://github.com/datalad/datalad-crawler/issues/55 I saw that the test marked as `@known_failure_v6_or_later` was not skipped although default version for the repositories now should be 7... and looking at the code the reason is obvious:
```python
def known_failure_v6_or_later(func):
    """Test decorator marking a test as known to fail in a v6+ test run

    If datalad.repo.version is set to 6 or later behaves like `known_failure`.
    Otherwise the original (undecorated) function is returned.
    """

    from datalad import cfg

    version = cfg.obtain("datalad.repo.version")
    if version and version >= 6:

        @known_failure
        @wraps(func)
        @attr('known_failure_v6_or_later')
        @attr('v6_or_later')
        def v6_func(*args, **kwargs):
            return func(*args, **kwargs)

        return v6_func

    return func
```

so we would skip only when we force default repo version to be >= 6, so with annex having v7 as default we wouldn't skip those (for better or for worse).

I am not sure yet if we should treat it as a bug (and fix it by eg considering also a version of annex) or a feature (that actually virtually no tests blew up) and start deprecating this decorator ;)
